cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically named entity recognition (NER) in Chinese language. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel CNN structure to capture glyph information from character graphs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses LSTM-CRF as a tagger and proposes a fusion representation learning method. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with NLP and machine learning techniques. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as NER is often used in information retrieval tasks.
